# WX-63 - keep the Docker build context (the HarderWare repo root) lean, and prevent a
# Windows-built bin/obj from poisoning the Linux build inside the container (the WX-62 lesson).
# Globs are **/ so nested build output at any depth is excluded, not just repo-root dirs.
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/.vs/
**/*.user
.git/
release/

# Secrets / per-machine config must never enter the build context (COPY . . would otherwise sweep
# them into the build cache): the container's DB-password config and observability's Grafana admin
# password. The image carries none of these — they are bind-mounted / injected at run time.
**/appsettings.local.json
**/.env
